  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate", 
    "date": "2017-03-30T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Veterans' Compensation Cost-of-Living Adjustment Act of 2017\n\nThis bill directs the Department of Veterans Affairs to increase, as of December 1, 2017, the rates of veterans' disability compensation, additional compensation for dependents, the clothing allowance for certain disabled veterans, and dependency and indemnity compensation for surviving spouses and children.\n\nEach such increase shall be the same percentage as the increase in benefits provided under title II (Old Age, Survivors and Disability Insurance) of the Social Security Act, on the same effective date."
  }, 
